  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Lots of security problems (including [the infamous TheDAO hack](http://hackingdistributed.com/2016/06/17/thoughts-on-the-dao-hack/)) can be prevented by using a pull payment strategy (as opposed to pushing payments with `send`).\r\n\r\nWe already have a simple [PullPayment](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-solidity/blob/v1.9.0/contracts/payment/PullPayment.sol) contract, but more comprehensive tools, documentation and examples are needed.\r\n\r\nA simple idea is to create a subclass of PullPayment that allows sending money to all pending payees at once.",
