    "body": "Thanks for the suggestion @mardlin! I love the idea.\nIt's a very good compromise solution, because a \"cron job\" that dispatches all the payments would have a cost (owner of the cron job has to pay for all the gas for withdrawals), but it would improve Pull Payments UX by a lot for users!\nSo, the contract owner is probably motivated to pay for that gas cost. Maybe we could implement another version of PullPayments with a \"withdrawAll\" method? \n",
